Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["FFTLog Lyman-alpha Appendix A Master Integrals", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"186af176-ae80-4b12-a8c8-96124eedc1be"],

Cell["\<\
This notebook wraps the companion source file `FFTLog_Lya_MasterIntegrals.wl` \
and keeps the workflow in the order requested by the theory-roundtrip \
playbook: derive first, compare to the paper second, and keep the audit trail \
visible in source comments. It is the higher-order continuation of the same \
LOS master-integral strategy used for the CLASS-PT galaxy notebook, now \
extended from the galaxy A1..C4 sector to the Lya A5..E8 sector.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6def1172-e148-4fdb-9c59-b3b9191494f9"],

Cell["\<\
The derivation layer uses the Schwinger-parameter generating function for

  Integral[(z.q)^n/(q^(2 nu1) |q-k|^(2 nu2)), q]

which yields closed mu-power coefficients in Gamma-function form. The \
reference layer now follows an exact triangular-basis audit of Appendix A of \
arXiv:2309.10133: the paper expressions are kept where they reconstruct \
exactly, while the local reference formulas for `B6`, `A7`, `C7`, `A8`, `B8`, \
`C8`, and `D8` are patched to the audited coefficients because those seven \
sectors fail the exact basis solve.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f3512cc0-730a-416d-a867-803d33c19ff3"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"5224c926-dee7-4001-9b47-2d6d5cc4d934"],

Cell["\<\
Module[{nbDir},
  Quiet@Remove[\"FFTLogMasterIntegralsDerivation`*\"];
  nbDir = Quiet@Check[NotebookDirectory[], $Failed];
  If[!StringQ[nbDir],
    nbDir = Quiet@Check[
      DirectoryName[NotebookFileName[EvaluationNotebook[]]],
      $Failed
    ]
  ];
  If[!StringQ[nbDir], nbDir = Directory[]];
  Get[FileNameJoin[{nbDir, \"FFTLog_Lya_MasterIntegrals.wl\"}]]
]\
\>", "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9853096208754873`*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "(Debug) In[10]:=",ExpressionUUID->"9ba5ea7a-c17e-44fa-8699-cc258b4a2aa0"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Hierarchy And Notation", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b5d90f17-2e14-4a8e-b55f-4cc4948ca4b6"],

Cell["\<\
This notebook extends the same scalar-master and LOS-coefficient hierarchy \
used in the matter and galaxy notebooks. Here the scalar master is denoted by \
J(nu1,nu2) for continuity with the Lya paper, but it is the same analytic \
object as the shared scalar master I(nu1,nu2).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ee3b1329-4f4c-44dc-bff3-653e493d2f43"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["LyANotationMap[]", "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "(Debug) In[11]:=",ExpressionUUID->"df3e5033-4428-4778-84d4-b73145d34330"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"\[LeftAssociation]", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"\<\"Scalar master integral J(nu1,nu2)\"\>", 
    "\[Rule]", "\<\"ScalarJ[nu1, nu2] = ScalarJMaster[nu1, nu2] = \
ScalarIMaster[nu1, nu2]\"\>"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"\<\"General LOS coefficient C_{n,m}\"\>", 
    "\[Rule]", "\<\"DerivedMuCoefficientByM[n, m, nu1, nu2]\"\>"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"\<\"Named Lya master-integral coefficients\"\>", 
    "\[Rule]", "\<\"DerivedCoefficient[name][nu1, nu2] with name in \
{A5..E8}\"\>"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"\<\"Audited Appendix A reference\"\>", 
    "\[Rule]", "\<\"ReferenceCoefficient[name][nu1, nu2] follows the paper \
where it passes exact triangular-basis reconstruction and uses locally \
corrected coefficients for {B6,A7,C7,A8,B8,C8,D8}\"\>"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"\<\"Extension relative to the galaxy notebook\"\>", 
    "\[Rule]", "\<\"This notebook continues the same LOS hierarchy beyond the \
CLASS-PT A1..C4 sector to the higher A5..E8 sector\"\>"}]}], 
  "\[RightAssociation]"}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.985632322775054*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "(Debug) Out[11]=",ExpressionUUID->"0f94f1e4-092d-4f0a-8b8f-4495cbd58147"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

