Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Notes", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"6b8b7aec-62e8-43c3-aa5f-704f57d6bcb2"],

Cell["\<\
Audit outcome for the Appendix A reference layer:

- `A5`, `B5`, `C5`, `A6`, `C6`, `D6`, `B7`, `D7`, and `E8` reconstruct the \
paper appendix exactly.
- `B6` differs in a local block of seven triangular-basis coefficients.
- `A7` keeps the leading `j[7,0]` term but every other term in the paper \
appendix is too small by a factor of `35`.
- `C7` has the correct magnitudes but the wrong overall sign.
- `A8` and `B8` keep the leading `j[8,0]` term but every other term is too \
small by `35`.
- `C8` keeps the leading `j[8,0]` term but every other term is too small by \
`105`.
- `D8` keeps the leading `j[8,0]` term but every other term is too small by \
`7`.

These patterns survive exact triangular-basis reconstruction and are not \
consistent with a hidden convention change such as `mu -> -mu`, `q <-> k-q`, \
or a different scalar-master normalization. The local reference expressions \
in the companion `.wl` file are therefore patched only in those seven sectors \
so the notebook can validate the audited Appendix A basis end to end.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c8f64520-1264-4dd4-9c1a-57ba6c5b6bc4"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
